title: Viera's Tyler Solnay wins Athlete of the Week vote
text:
Viera's Tyler Solnay wins Athlete of the Week vote FLORIDA TODAY 2:27 p.m. EDT October 1, 2015 FLORIDA TODAY's Athlete of the Week sponsored by Community Credit Union (Photo: Athlete of the Week sponsored by Community Credit Union) 
Congratulations to Viera High golfer Tyler Solnay , FLORIDA TODAYâ€™s high school Athlete of the Week for the week for Sept. 21-28. 
Solnay shot a 33 at The Majors Golf Club in Palm Bay on Sept. 24. Solnay was 3-under par for nine holes in a victory against Heritage. 
Solnay collected 51 percent of the online vote out of five athletes represented. More than 1,000 votes were received. 
Viera High golfer has been voted FLORIDA TODAY's Athlete of the Week. (Photo: Photo courtesy of Viera High School.) 
Second place was Merritt Island Christian volleyball player Olivia Powers (29 percent), followed by Heritage High football player Daeshawn Mills (10 percent), Titusville High bowler Brandi Washington (6 percent) and Holy Trinity cross country runner Shelby Smith (4 percent). 
Be sure to vote this upcoming Monday for the next Athlete of the Week. Read or Share this story: http://on.flatoday.com/1FIOh0Z TOP VIDEOS
